{meta: title Last Cowboy Song}
{meta: artist Waylon Jennings}
{meta: composer Ed Bruce and Ron Peterson}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]This is the last cowboy song
[F]The end of a hundred year waltz
[G7]The music is sad as they're singing along
[C]Another piece of America's lost
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
He rides a feed lot and clerks in a market
[G7]On weekends selling tobacco and beer
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
His days are spent surrounded by fences
[C]But he'll dream tonight of when fences weren't here
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
The Old Chisholm Trail is covered by concrete
[G7]They drive 'em to market in fifty foot rigs
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
They’ll roll by his graveside and they don’t even notice
[C]Like living and dying was all that he did
{end_of_verse}

